name: Domain Investigation
creator: 7a7f9e2c-7774-4221-8558-986f5708fd17
description: Enriches URLs, Emails, Domains, and IP addresses with WHOIS information.  Will create domain entities and link to URLs and Emails.  Will set any domain that is less than 180 days old as suspicious.  Checks to see if domains are look a like domains.

steps.description:
Microsoft threat intel describes a phishing campaign that uses DGA domains,
  free email services, and compromised email accounts to send massive numbers of phishing emails.
  These emails use open redirector URLs that begin with a distinct pattern:
    hxxps://t[.]domain[.]tld/r/?
  This rule can be improved to look for DGA senders, free email providers, brand
  impersonation content in the body, etc.
steps.name: Condition

steps.description: Query WHOIS servers for domain registration information.  Supports IP Addresses, URLs, Email, Domains.  Supports creation of DOMAIN entities linked to target entity and a domain age threshold to set the entity to suspicious.
steps.name: Enrichment_Whois
